{
  "stem": "16163.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that's where my mother worked, and she was sent from there to this big [INAUDIBLE] place.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And Mr.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Gottesman, who was my father-in-law, was the one who gave out the medication.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And when she told him that I was so sick-- [INAUDIBLE] she must have been crying, whatever-- that I was so sick and that I'm hospitalized, he gave her I don't know what you-- [? glucosa. ?]",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know what [? glucosa ?] is?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's like a-- sugar from-- from grapes-- grape sugar.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they made liquids out of it, and people got it as-- I don't know for what illnesses-- as injections.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he gave my mother those whenever she went there and told her when she sees me to give it to me, to break it open, and let me drink it-- that I could drink it so it would give me energy.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's how we got into medication.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, there was very little medication for what I needed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was very lucky that one of the doctors [INAUDIBLE] Dr.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Schwartz, who didn't survive it either, a young doctor, he was friends with a Czech-- [?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Czechnik. ?] A [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Czechnik ?] is a a Czech policeman who worked for the Germans in-- in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this man would go back every week or every second week took Prague on a furlough.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this doctor told him to bring medication from Prague, if he could bring this and this medication.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I got that, and it really saved my life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was injections of bee poison, which is for-- specialized for rheumatoid fever at the time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So this is how I made it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father, believe it or not, I don't know what he was really working.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
